text.text: murad sammour likes this

🎯 𝗧𝗵𝗿𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗦𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗔𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝗕𝗶𝗴 𝗠𝗶𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗲! 🎯

I’m incredibly excited and pleased to share that I’ve officially earned the 𝗣𝗠𝗜-𝗔𝗖𝗣® (𝗔𝗴𝗶𝗹𝗲 𝗖𝗲𝗿𝘁𝗶𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗱 𝗣𝗿𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗲𝗿) certification — with an 𝗔𝗯𝗼𝘃𝗲 𝗧𝗮𝗿𝗴𝗲𝘁 score!

This marks my 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗿𝗱 𝗺𝗮𝗷𝗼𝗿 𝗰𝗲𝗿𝘁𝗶𝗳𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝘆𝗲𝗮𝗿, and I’m deeply grateful for the learning journey that each milestone represents:
🏅 𝗣𝗠𝗣® – 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗠𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗳𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 (earned earlier in 2025)
🏅 𝗣𝗦𝗠 𝗜 – 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗳𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 𝗦𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗺 𝗠𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 (earned in September 2025)
🏅 𝗣𝗠𝗜-𝗔𝗖𝗣® – 𝗔𝗴𝗶𝗹𝗲 𝗖𝗲𝗿𝘁𝗶𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗱 𝗣𝗿𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗲𝗿 (earned recently)

Together, these achievements represent an exciting step forward in strengthening my skills in 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗹𝗲𝗮𝗱𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽, 𝗮𝗴𝗶𝗹𝗲 𝗱𝗲𝗹𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆, 𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗼𝘃𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻, 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮𝗱𝗮𝗽𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝘁𝗲𝗮𝗺𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸 — while reinforcing my commitment to 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗶𝗻𝘂𝗼𝘂𝘀 𝗴𝗿𝗼𝘄𝘁𝗵 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗹𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴.

A heartfelt thank-you to Aurora Technologies for their ongoing support, encouragement, and training, and to MILESTONES MENA for their excellent Agile in Action program and for hosting the exam.

Here’s to continuous learning, embracing agility, empowering teams, and driving impact! 🚀

#PMIACP #PMP #PSM #Agile #ProjectManagement #Leadership #ContinuousLearning #AuroraTechnologies #MilestonesMENA

text.text: murad sammour likes this

For over four decades, Abanos has redefined joinery through precision, creativity, and manufacturing operations spanning 23,775.89 sqm. Guided by eco-conscious practices, we integrate sustainable wooden boards sourced from regional manufacturers into our work—supporting local industries while setting new benchmarks in responsible craftsmanship.
 
Our latest curated collection of bespoke joinery products exemplifies this approach. Utilizing Palm Strand Board (PSB®)—an engineered wooden board upcycled from pruned palm fronds—our team has developed high-performance furniture solutions that combine functional efficiency with refined aesthetics.
 
From folding room dividers engineered for flexible spaces, to compact tables, minimalist chairs, modern padded seating, and even functional art, including circular perpetual calendar, each creation demonstrates Abanos’ expertise in advanced engineering, specialized finishing, and tailored fabrication.
 
This portfolio represents how sustainable innovation and technical mastery converge to deliver interior solutions that are durable, responsible, and design-forward.
 
Discover Abanos’ custom joinery solutions at https://abanos.ae/
 
#abanos #sustainabledesign #sustainablejoinery #sustainablebuildingmaterial #palmstrandboard

Abanos delivered a custom-designed exhibition stand for the ECC Group, to be placed at ICOM Dubai 2025, showcasing its expertise in turning complex ideas into reality. The event brought together museums and cultural institutions to advance sustainable, ethical, and innovative practices in heritage preservation—a vision that Abanos supports by transforming ambitious concepts into meticulously crafted, functional, and visually striking exhibition solutions.

From precise wood cutting, intricate molding, and detailed carving to high-quality veneering, laminating, and finishing, our skilled craftsmen bring every vision to life. Leveraging advanced machinery, high-speed painting lines, and sustainable practices, Abanos consistently transforms visionary designs into functional, visually striking, and bespoke solutions across residential, commercial, and specialized sectors.

Learn more about our range of services at https://abanos.ae/

Twelve years later, it’s clear that sustainable success is not only about strategy it’s about the people you build it with.

Looking forward to the next chapter.

DesertBoard is proud to have won the “Sustainable Building Material Manufacturer of the Year” Award at the Sustainability Excellence Awards 2025, organised by Gulf News in collaboration with BeingShe.

This prestigious recognition reinforces our leadership in sustainable innovation in building material and highlights our ongoing contribution to the UAE’s Net Zero 2050 vision. As the world’s first manufacturer of engineered palm-based wooden boards — known as Palm Strand Board (PSB®) — DesertBoard continues to redefine the future of construction by transforming agricultural byproducts into high-performance, eco-friendly building materials—reducing reliance on imports and promoting circular economy practices.

Winning this award signifies more than industry acknowledgment; it reflects our dedication to supporting the nation’s sustainability agenda, strengthening the local economy, and advancing environmentally conscious manufacturing within the region.

We are grateful for this honor and remain committed to driving impactful change as we continue shaping a greener and more resilient future for the UAE and beyond.
  
#sustainabilityexcellenceaward #palmstrandboard #sustainablebuildingmaterial #desertboard #gulfnews #beingshe

text.text:
His Highness Sheikh Hamdan bin Mohammad bin Rashid Al Maktoum inaugurated Hewi Nad Al Sheba, the first community space launched under the Hewi Dubai initiative.

Engineering Contracting Company (ECC Contracting) is proud to have been the main contractor for this landmark project at Nad Al Shiba Fourth, delivering it ahead of schedule. Executed under a Design & Build contract for Dubai Municipality, the project was completed within just 3 months, including design, with actual construction achieved in only 2.5 months.

Spanning approximately 10,000 m², Hewi Nad Al Sheba honours Emirati heritage while offering a modern, vibrant hub for community interaction—reflecting ECC Contracting’s commitment to precision, quality, and innovative delivery in community-focused developments.

‘Hewi’ is a traditional outdoor space where families and neighbours come together, reflecting the spirit of belonging and community connection. Hewi Nad Al Sheba has been developed by the Dubai Municipality, in partnership with Dubai Future Foundation and Ferjan Dubai.
 
Explore ECC Contracting’s iconic projects across the UAE: https://lnkd.in/de9hWQgN
